		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, it's a never-ending struggle.  Finding and removing spams isn't my idea of fun (today is my 25th birthday, the spammers are giving me a gift of grief, heh).
<br />
<br />And I've been noticing more and more that phpBB's ban control is a total POS.  I try to remove the old bans when adding new ones so the list doesn't become infinite, but it seems to randomly choose to add new bans to the top or bottom of the list..  I'm just assuming that a giant ban list is gonna overwork the server.  Plus I think most spams are 'hit and run' basically (I'm seeing identical spams from different IPs).  Quietust recommended a mod that improves it, I'll install it sometime eventually.
<br />
<br />Forcing people to register won't stop the spammers, it might slow them down a bit.  We're using probably the most popular forum software on the net, so it comes with the territory unfortunately.  They even get past the captcha thing.
<br />
<br />But yeah, I'll assign some moderators.  tepples, you can be one if you want.  And anyone else who's here as often or more often than me.  Anyone else just reply here to apply.  We won't need an army of mods, just a few good ones.
<br />
<br />Bregalad makes a good point tho, if the spamfloods don't get under control it's gonna start to stink the place up.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
