		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Is there no plugins for phpbb to block post that includes link with specific words in the url? that could be pretty effective way of blocking atleast these latest spams  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" />
<br />
<br />edit:
<br />looked through the security things on the phpbb pages and there seems to be some intresting that might help:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.phpbb.com/phpBB/catdb.php?cat=57">http://www.phpbb.com/phpBB/catdb.php?cat=57</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />some I found:
<br />
<br />[2.0.13] disable spambots
<br />This mod uses cryptographic signing techniques to ensure that any comment submissions have occurred from an appropriate
<br />comment form (stopping simple random-submission bots)
<br />
<br />[2.0.12] Visual Confirmation for Guests
<br />Adds visual confirmation for guest posts, eliminating spam. 
<br />
<br />[2.0.18] Block Open Proxy Registrants
<br />Blocks those attempting to register from open proxies. 
<br />(but this one can be troublesome for those members who isn't spamers and using proxies)
<br />
<br />..I don't know, maybe this are not that good at all.. what do you all thinks?

		

